TIETO.HE.summary: TietoEVRY Oyj operates as a software and services company. It operates through Digital Experience, Hybrid Infra, Industry Software, and Product Development Services segments. The Digital Experience segment provides consulting services, including design of service experiences, smart use of data, IT architecture consulting, and business process and change management, as well as system integration, and application development and management. The Hybrid Infra segment offers enterprises with life cycle management of IT infrastructure, which covers a variety of technologies. The Industry Software segment provides with industry-specific software products for business-critical processes of clients in the financial services, public and healthcare, and welfare sectors, as well as in the forest industry, and the energy and oil and gas segments. The Product Development Services segment offers software R&D services with a focus on the telecom sector, as well as new domains, such as automotive serving the communications infrastructure, consumer electronics, and semiconductor companies, and the automotive industry. The company also provides software advisory and consulting services, and industry specific software; engages in the design, implementation, and maintenance of customized solutions and IT operations. It operates in Finland, Sweden, Norway, Austria, the Baltic countries, Russia, and internationally. TietoEVRY has collaboration with VTT to bring European cybersecurity and research expertise to automotive software development. The company was formerly known as Tieto Oyj and changed its name to TietoEVRY Oyj in December 2019. TietoEVRY Oyj was founded in 1968 and is headquartered in Espoo, Finland.

UUTEC.HE.summary: Plc Uutechnic Group Oyj develops and manufactures equipment and services for enhancing production processes in the process industries worldwide. Its products include agitators, pressure vessels, process and storage tanks, reactors, and heat exchangers, as well as various types of long welded and machined axially symmetrical parts, such as rolls, cylinders, pipes, and cones. The company primarily serves hydrometallurgy and the mining, pulp, paper, and food industries, as well as the fertilizer and other chemical, and environmental technology industries. Plc Uutechnic Group Oyj is based in Uusikaupunki, Finland. As of January 12, 2021, Plc Uutechnic Group Oyj operates as a subsidiary of SPX Flow Technology Norderstedt GmbH.

V4OC.F.summary: Kojamo Oyj, a private residential real estate company, provides rental apartments and housing services in Finland. The company rents and manages apartments under the Lumo brand name. As of December 31, 2019, it operated 35,272 rental apartments. The company was formerly known as VVO Group plc and changed its name to Kojamo Oyj in March 2017. Kojamo Oyj was founded in 1969 and is headquartered in Helsinki, Finland.

V5W.F.summary: Afarak Group Oyj engages in the production and supply of chrome products worldwide. It operates through two segments, FerroAlloys and Speciality Alloys. The Ferro Alloys segment produces chrome ore, charge chrome, medium carbon ferrochrome, and silicomanganese. The Specialty Alloys segment offers specialized low carbon and ultra low carbon ferrochrome. The company also exports chrome ore. It sells its products in the United States, China, Africa, Finland, and Other European Union countries. The company was formerly known as Ruukki Group Plc and changed its name to Afarak Group Plc in July 2013. Afarak Group Oyj is based in Helsinki, Finland.

VAIAS.HE.summary: Vaisala Oyj engages in the weather and environmental, and industrial measurement business serving weather related and industrial markets. The company's products include industrial measurement systems, such as indoor measurement and process control instruments, continuous monitoring systems, instruments for power transformers, and technology for liquid concentration measurement; and weather and environmental solutions comprising sensors and instruments, systems and solutions, and digital and data as a service products. It also offers technical support, calibration and repair, system maintenance, consulting, training, project, modernization, and continuous monitoring system services, as well as online stores. The company serves weather-dependent markets, such as meteorology, ground transportation, aviation, railway, maritime, safety and security, renewable energy, and ambient air quality; and various industrial customers includes life science and power industry. It has operations Europe, the Middle East, Africa, North and South Americas, and the Asia Pacific. The company was founded in 1936 and is headquartered in Vantaa, Finland.

VALMT.HE.summary: Valmet Oyj, together with its subsidiaries, develops and supplies process technologies, automation, and services for the pulp, paper, and energy industries. The company offers solutions and services for the pulping industry, including chemical pulping, wood handling, cooking and fiber line, pulp drying, chemical recovery, air emission control, other value-adding processes, dissolving pulping, mechanical pulping, recycled fiber, and automation for pulp. It also provides technologies, automation products, and services for board and paper production, such as recycled fiber, stock preparation, board and paper machines, services for board and paper, and automation for board and paper; and technologies, automation products, and services for tissue production. In addition, the company offers energy solutions, BFB and CFB boilers, gasifiers, power and heating plants, air emission control, industrial internet solutions, and services and automation for energy. Further, it provides solutions to paper converting, mining and chemical, food and biotechnology, and pharmaceuticals industries, as well as commercial laundries; and automation for liquefied natural gas and biogas infrastructure, wastewater, oil and gas, and marine industries. Valmet Oyj is headquartered in Espoo, Finland.

VALOE.HE.summary: Valoe Oyj develops and sells solar energy technology products worldwide. The company offers automated production technology for solar modules; production lines for modules, solar modules, and special components for solar modules; and solar cells. It also provides one-sided interdigitated back contact (IBC) and bifacial IBC back contact modules; and solar power plants and systems. The company was formerly known as Cencorp Oyj and changed its name to Valoe Oyj in May 2015. Valoe Oyj was founded in 1948 and is headquartered in Mikkeli, Finland.

VERK.HE.summary: Verkkokauppa.com Oyj operates as an online consumer electronics retailer in Finland. The company also operates four retail stores. In addition, it offers installation and maintenance services, subscription sales, and visibility sales. The company was founded in 1992 and is headquartered in Helsinki, Finland.

VIAFIN.HE.summary: Viafin Service Oyj provides industrial maintenance, piping and equipment maintenance, and installation services in Finland. Its services include industrial piping, hydraulics and instrument piping, and mechanical welding, as well as industrial and mechanical installation works on industrial shutdowns. It serves pulp, energy, chemical, and forest industries. The company is based in Kurikka, Finland. Viafin Service Oyj is a subsidiary of Viafin Oy.

VIK1V.HE.summary: Viking Line ABP, together with its subsidiaries, provides passenger and cargo carrier services. The company offers its services using seven vessels between Finland, Sweden, and Estonia; and owns 13 buses. It also provides cargo shipment and freight forwarding services. The company also has operations in other Baltic countries, Poland, Denmark, Norway, and Russia. Viking Line ABP was founded in 1959 and is headquartered in Mariehamn, Finland.

WE3.F.summary: Sievi Capital Oyj is a private equity arm of Jussi Capital Ltd specializing in capital investments in small and medium-sized enterprises, in turnover and net result in the medium term and long term. The firm focuses on industrial companies, either listed or unlisted. It primarily invests in investments in Denmark, Finland, Iceland, Norway, and Sweden. It seeks to acquire a significant holding and seeks a board seat on its investee companies. The firm also makes financial investments in shares, ETF instruments, structured products, corporate bonds, and other fixed-income investments. It seeks to have majority stakes. For financial investments, it holds its investments for less than three years. It seeks to make balance sheet investments. The firm was formerly known as Scanfil plc and changed its name to Sievi Capital Oyj in 2011. Sievi Capital Oyj is based in Helsinki, Finland.

WUF1V.HE.summary: Wulff-YhtiÃ¶t Oyj, together with its subsidiaries, sells and markets office supplies, facility management products, catering solutions, IT supplies, ergonomics, first aid, air purifiers, and other products for worksites. The company also provides printing services, data management solutions, ICT outsourcing services, and large-format printing services; maintenance and remote monitoring solutions; meeting and event catering services; exhibition; first aid solutions, products, and training services; novelties for everyday life; and professional solutions for post-treatment of paper, and products for worksites and real estates. YEINT.HE.summary: Yleiselektroniikka Oyj imports and sells electronic components and tools to Finland, Russia, and the Baltics. The company offers 3D printing products, antennas and accessories, audio/video products, cables and accessories, converters, KVMs, networking products, PC and car accessories, telecommunication and power products, wall outlets, and AVs. It also provides batteries, chemicals, connectors, cooling products and fans, development kits, electric accessories, LED components, lighting and RF products, mechanical components, passives, relays, semiconductors, sounders, switches, tapes, and literature products. In addition, the company offers baking ovens, cable cutting and strip tools, cleaning and dry storage products, clothing and personal protection products, component counter and lead handling products, crimping dies and machines, dispensers, fume extractors, labels, lamps, microscopes, mounting accessories, PCBs and accessories, packing products, safety and soldering products, ultrasonic cleaners, and weighting products, as well as ESD and protection products. Further, it provides air quality/flow meters, bags and carrying cases, battery testers, cable locators and testers, calipers, clamp and distance meters, component and earth ground testers, electrical and FO testers, endoscopes, frequency counters, function generators, installation and insulation testers, IR windows, lasers, LAN and machine testers, light intensity meters, loggers, multimeters and its related software, oscilloscopes, phase rotation indicators, power quality meters, process calibrators and precision pressure gauges, radiation meters, solar power and sound level meters, power analyzers, surface testers, tachometers, temperature/humidity meters, test leads and probes, thermal cameras and accessories, vibration testers, and visual inspection and other tools. It sells products through stores and catalogues. The company was founded in 1969 and is based in Espoo, Finland.

YIT.F.summary: YIT Oyj provides construction services for industrial and public sectors, and residential customers primarily in Finland, Russia, the Baltic countries, the Czech Republic, Poland, and Slovakia. It operates through three segments: Housing Finland and CEE, Housing Russia, and Business Premises and Infrastructure. The company develops and constructs housing, holiday homes, apartments, and various residential areas, as well as offices, shopping malls, public facilities and buildings, assisted living facilities, production and logistics premises, and other business premises; maintains property; undertakes renovation projects; and provides road and street maintenance services. It also constructs roads, bridges, tunnels, rail and metro stations, ports, and parking facilities, as well as energy, water supply, and industrial plants; offers mining and reinforcement, and tunneling services; undertakes civil engineering, earthworks, and foundation works; and produces asphalt, and re-used asphalt pavements and surfaces, as well as provides solutions for the paving industry. In addition, the company offers construction machinery and equipment rental, and IT services. YIT Oyj was founded in 1912 and is headquartered in Helsinki, Finland.
